                  It is most certaine, and by experience found to be true, that as the rivers daily carrie much earth with them into the sea, so the sea sends backe againe much slime and sand to the earth, which in some places, and namely in the North part of Deuonshire is found to bee a marveilous great commoditie for the inriching of the soyle.
                  Now as the Earth is nothing diminished in regard of the dimensions, (the measure thereof from the Surface to the Center being the same, as it was at the first Creation,) So neither is the fatnes &amp; fruitfulnes thereof, at least-wise since the flood, or in regard of duration alone, any whit impaired; though it haue yeelded such store of increase by the space of so many reuolutions of ages, yet hee that made it, continually reneweth the face thereof, as the Psalmist speakes, by turning all things 104: 30. which spring from it into it againe. Saith one, 
                  
                     
